TextEng: Could I ask you some questions?
Me want ask questions.
Goodbye.
Do you know of any cults in the city?
You knows about cults, maybe?
What is going on in Luskan?
What going on in city?
Can I ask you some directions?
Me need directions.
Who are you?
Who be you?
I want to speak to you about Erb's ring.
Me want talk 'bout Erb's ring.
Maybe we could work out some kind of deal.
Text: 어떤 거래를 할 수 있을 것 같은데.

TextEng: I'm not going to argue with you. Hand over the ring... now.
Text: 더는 말다툼 안 할거야. 반지를 내놔... 당장.

TextEng: Fine. Keep it. I want to ask you about something else anyway.
Text: 좋아. 가져. 어차피 다른 걸 물어보고 싶었어.

TextEng: We make deal, maybe?
Me no argues. You gives ring... now.
Text: 더는 말 안 해. 반지 내놔... 지금.

TextEng: Fine. Me no want it. Me want ask 'bout something else.
Text: 좋아. 그건 필요 없어. 다른 거 물어볼래.

TextEng: 1000 gold? Deal.
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> That's outrageous! I won't give more than 250 gp!
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 말도 안 돼! 금화 250개 이상은 안 줘!

TextEng: Are you trying to cheat me?! Don't make me angry...
Text: 날 속이려는 거야?! 화나게 하지 마...

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> That too much. Me give 250 gp.
You cheats me?! You makes me very angry...
<StartCheck>[Insight]</Start> Take the 250 gp. Do you really want that ring, now?
Text: <StartCheck>[통찰]</Start> 금화 250개 받아. 정말 그 반지 원해?

TextEng: 400 gold? Deal.
250 gp? Deal.
I'm done haggling. Give me the ring... now.
Me not argue no more. You gives ring... now!
Text: 더는 안 따져. 반지 내놔... 지금!

TextEng: I can't afford to spend that much gold on this.
Text: 이걸 위해 그렇게 많은 금화를 쓸 여유가 없어.

TextEng: Me not got that much gold for spend on this.
I can't afford to spend that much on this.
Text: 이걸 위해 그렇게 많이 쓸 여유가 없어.

TextEng: Me not afford that much for this.
I don't have 400 gold to spend on this.
Me no got 400 gold to spend on this.
I don't believe you - hand over the ring now!
Text: 못 믿겠어 - 지금 당장 반지 내놔!

TextEng: Hey - if you don't have it I want my coin back!
Text: 이봐 - 그게 없다면 내 금화 돌려줘!

TextEng: What do you mean you've been robbed?
I guess I'll be going, then.
Me no believe you - you gives ring now!
Text: 안 믿어 - 지금 당장 반지 내놔!

TextEng: Hey - you no gives ring, me want me money back!
Text: 이봐 - 반지 안 주면, 내 금화 돌려줘!

TextEng: What you mean you be robbed?
Me guess me go now.
That's not fair!
I'm warning you... give me my coin. Now.
Fine, keep the coin.
That not fair!
Me warns you... you gives coin back. Now.
Fine, you keeps coin.
What about your husband? What will he think of the ring?
Text: 남편은? 그 반지에 대해 뭐라고 할까?

TextEng: What abouts husband? What he thinks of ring?
Be reasonable. Let's talk about this, shall we?
You and me talks about it, okay?
Why do you think Erb wants his ring back?
Text: 왜 어브가 자기 반지를 돌려받으려 한다고 생각하지?

TextEng: Why you thinks gnome wants ring back?
Text: 왜 노움이 반지 돌려받고 싶다 생각해?

TextEng: Fine. Hand over the ring, then... now.
Fine. You gives ring... now.
<StartCheck>[Finesse]</Start> How about the fact that you've broken Section 12 of Luskan's gift-receiving code?
Text: <StartCheck>[요령]</Start> 러스칸 선물 수령 규정 12조를 어긴 사실은 어때?

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Threaten]</Start> Ignorance is no excuse. I'm afraid I'll have to place you under arrest.
Text: <StartCheck>[위협]</Start> 몰랐다는 건 변명이 안 돼. 유감이지만 널 체포해야겠어.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Lie]</Start> Oh, yes. You see, that ring is quite valuable, and Erb didn't pay his taxes on it.
Text: <StartCheck>[거짓말]</Start> 아, 그래. 그 반지는 꽤 값나가는 건데, 어브가 세금을 안 냈거든.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> You don't want me to turn you in, do you? So just give me the ring.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 내가 신고하길 바라진 않겠지? 그러니 반지를 줘.

TextEng: Er, yes... just a joke. Ha ha!
<StartCheck>[Lie]</Start> It means I'll have to arrest Erb unless the ring is returned.
Text: <StartCheck>[거짓말]</Start> 반지가 돌아오지 않으면 어브를 체포해야 한다는 뜻이야.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Lie]</Start> It means you'll have to pay the taxes... or return the ring.
Text: <StartCheck>[거짓말]</Start> 네가 세금을 내야 해... 아니면 반지를 돌려주든가.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Lie]</Start> It means I'll have to arrest you. Sorry.
<StartCheck>[Lie]</Start> I guess Erb was trying to get you into trouble. He must not love you as much as you thought.
Text: <StartCheck>[거짓말]</Start> 어브가 널 곤란에 빠뜨리려 했던 것 같네. 네가 생각한 만큼 널 사랑하진 않는 모양이야.

TextEng: Oh, nothing. Forget I said anything.
Text: 아니야, 아무것도 아냐. 방금 한 말은 잊어.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> You really want to keep the ring of a man who doesn't love you?
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 너를 사랑하지도 않는 남자의 반지를 정말 계속 갖고 있고 싶어?

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> You wants ring of gnome who no loves you?
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 너 사랑 안 하는 노움 반지, 너 갖고 싶어?

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Erb doesn't love you, let me assure you.
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Gnome not love you, me knows.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 노움 너 안 사랑해, 나 알아.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Insight]</Start> It doesn't matter. You've broken Section 12 of Luskan's gift-receiving code, m'lady.
Text: <StartCheck>[통찰]</Start> 그건 중요하지 않아. 러스칸 선물 수령 규정 12조를 어겼어, 부인.

TextEng: He's frightened of your husband. You want him to get hurt?
Text: 그는 네 남편을 두려워해. 그가 다치길 바라는 거야?

TextEng: He scared of husband. You wants gnome hurt?
Text: 그, 남편 무서워해. 노움 다치길 원해?

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Well, Erb thinks you must, since you won't return the ring.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 그래, 네가 반지를 안 돌려주니 어브는 네가 그러길 바란다고 생각하더라.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Gnome thinks so, since you not gives ring back.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 너 반지 안 주니, 노움 그리 생각해.

TextEng: Fine. I'm sorry.
Fine. Me sorry.
<StartCheck>[Intimidate]</Start> You think I can't take your guards? Try me.
Text: <StartCheck>[위협]</Start> 네 경비들을 못 이길 것 같아? 한번 해봐.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Intimidate]</Start> You thinks me not take guards? You funny lady.
Text: <StartCheck>[위협]</Start> 나 경비 못 이긴다 생각해? 너 웃긴 여자야.

TextEng: That's it! I'm through playing around!
That it! Me done being nice!!
Forget it. I'm leaving.
Forgets it. Me go, anyways.
I don't believe you - hand over the ring now!
What do you mean you've been robbed?
I guess I'll be going, then.
Me no believe you - you gives ring now!
Text: 나 안 믿어-지금 당장 반지 줘!

TextEng: What you mean you be robbed?
Me guess me go now.
